name: media_png_valid_zero_length_idat_before_data
description: |
  A valid 1x1 RGBA PNG with an empty IDAT chunk immediately before the IDAT
  chunk that carries the zlib stream. PNG image data is the concatenation of the
  data fields of consecutive IDAT chunks, so a zero-length IDAT contributes no
  bytes but is still a legal chunk with its own CRC. Decoders that assume every
  IDAT must contain compressed bytes may reject this valid stream.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG Suite documents "different numbers and sizes of IDAT chunks" as a
  decoder test class, and the PNG specification defines IDAT chunking:
  https://www.libpng.org/pub/png/pngsuite.html
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#11IDAT
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "valid-png"
  - "idat"
  - "chunking"
  - "zero-length"
---
